<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-83-0005 </DOCNO><TEXT>Rapid developments in genetic, molecular biology and general microbiologyturn the attention of both the scientists and environmental policy-makersto questions related with the release of genetically engineered microorganisms.At present, however, only little is known about the possible environmentalconsequences of such releases. The 1st international conference 'Regem1', which was held in April 1988 in Cardiff (UK), reflected an actuallevel of knowledge in this field. Based on this knowledge and also onecological premisses, a further need for research has been indicatedin this paper.</TEXT></DOC>